================================================================================
PART 2: Business Source License 1.1 (Server)
================================================================================

The following components are licensed under the Business Source License 1.1:

- ALICE-DB Server (network protocol, storage engine, query parser)
- Persistence layer
- WAL (Write-Ahead Log)
- Segment management

Licensor:             Moroya Sakamoto
Licensed Work:        ALICE-DB Server
Change Date:          Four years from the date the Licensed Work is published
Change License:       Apache License, Version 2.0

Terms:

The Licensor hereby grants you the right to copy, modify, create derivative
works, redistribute, and make non-production use of the Licensed Work.

Additional Use Grant:

You may make production use of the Licensed Work, provided such use does not
include offering the Licensed Work to third parties on a hosted or embedded
basis which is competitive with Licensor's products.

"Competitive" means a product or service that provides database-as-a-service
(DBaaS) functionality substantially similar to the Licensed Work.

For clarity, the following uses are permitted WITHOUT a commercial license:
- Internal use within your organization
- Building applications that use ALICE-DB as a dependency
- Offering applications (not databases) that happen to use ALICE-DB internally
- Research and educational purposes
- Personal projects

The following uses REQUIRE a commercial license:
- Offering ALICE-DB as a managed database service (DBaaS)
- Embedding ALICE-DB in a product sold as a database solution
- Cloud providers offering ALICE-DB as a service option

================================================================================
PART 3: Commercial License (Enterprise)
================================================================================

The following products require a commercial license:

ALICE-DB Enterprise
-------------------
- Automatic S3 Tiering (cold data offloading)
- Advanced Clustering (Raft consensus, auto-sharding)
- Audit & Security (RBAC, LDAP/SSO integration)
- Visual Dashboard (GUI management)
- Priority support
- Annual contract

Target: Large enterprises, data centers
Pricing: Contact for details

For commercial licensing inquiries:
  https://extoria.co.jp/en

================================================================================
Summary
================================================================================

| Use Case                        | Core (Free) | Server     | Enterprise  |
|---------------------------------|-------------|------------|-------------|
| Personal / Educational          | MIT         | BSL (Free) | -           |
| Internal business use           | MIT         | BSL (Free) | Optional    |
| Building applications           | MIT         | BSL (Free) | Optional    |
| Offering as DBaaS               | MIT         | Commercial | Required    |
| Enterprise (HA, Clustering)     | MIT         | BSL (Free) | Required    |

The Core library is always FREE under MIT license.
The Server is FREE for non-competitive use under BSL 1.1.
Enterprise features provide additional value for large-scale operations.

